parameters: Hehe~ Hikaru, what are you doing here?
I was wondering if there's anything I can help with.
Will you help me? Hmm, I wonder what there is...
Ah, I'm planning to go fishing now, wanna do it together?
Are you going fishing? Did you bring a fishing rod?
However, I don't see anything around here.

She doesn't seem to have anything in her hands either, and
she's wearing a skimpy swimsuit...
Hehehe... Lord Hikaru, you still have a long way to go!
She showed me a snorkel and a spear gun.

A crab is proudly perched on top of this item, dripping
with water. Did it get left in the water...?
Or was it dropped?
Oh, you already caught a crab.
Akane, who was surprised, dropped her equipment.

The small crab, which was proudly opening and closing its
claws to show off its appearance, quickly disappeared
in surprise.
Ah... I also unknowingly succeeded in hunting...!
Anyway, I was trying to catch fish with this.

The way to hold the center of gravity was a little
difficult, but surprisingly, the weight itself is very
light.

Hikaru, do you want to try too? I'll let you have your first
experience!
Where did you pick this up from?
I found it at the cottage!
No, let's not say that out loud.
(I wonder who is the closest one?)
Wow! Amazing! I caught it in one try!
Hikaru definitely has the talent of a Yasu King!

Stop calling me a nickname like King Hikaru that sounds
like a named monster at the beginning of a journey to
conquer a school like Yasu King.

And then, I caught fish alternately with Akane using a
spear.

As I sit on the beach and watch Akane swimming, I feel
like I understand why there are more spectators at the
school pool on the days she practices.

Her gentle movements of her waist and legs felt like a
mermaid from a fairy tale.
Lord Hikaru, Lord Hikaru! I have caught it again!
If I open my mouth, the illusion will be shattered.

Hehe, it's okay to praise me a little more, you know? Praise
me, praise me!

And then, I returned to the cottage with Akane, holding a
bucket full of fish.
Ah, Hikaru! Shall we try it again?
(I wonder who is the closest one?)
Hikaru definitely has the talent of a king!

Stop calling me a nickname like King Yasu that sounds
like a named monster at the beginning of a journey to
conquer such a school.

And then, taking turns with Akane, we caught fish with our
hands.

As I sat by the beach and watched Akane swimming, I
couldn't help but feel like I understood why the school
pool would have more spectators on the days she
practices.

Her gentle movements of her waist and legs felt like a
mermaid from a fairy tale.
Lord Hikaru, Lord Hikaru! I have caught another one!
When I open my mouth, the illusion shatters.

Hehe, it's okay to praise me a little more, you know? Praise
me, praise me!

And then, I returned to the cottage with Akane, holding a
bucket full of fish.

I have already cleared this event. Would you like to do
the event again?
It's not fair! You're heavy, so be careful!
Well, if that's the case, there's no helping it.
Guh, there's sand in my mouth...

It's because I used a ground technique on the sandy beach,
right?!

I'll give Akane-kun, who refuses to admit defeat, a chance
to make a comeback.
Alright! The one who catches it first wins, okay?
Let me know when you're ready!
Nin nin. I have emerged victorious.
No way... for someone like me... to lose in the water...
It seems like my ninja training was not enough, ninnin.
Ugh... I don't even want to comment on it anymore.

Since I won, the winner shall exercise their rights as the
winner, de gozaru.

The winner's rights? Is this the first time I've heard of
that!?
I did say it, in my heart.
Akane, you're smarter than I thought.
Are you getting angry!? I'm seriously getting angry!
Anyway, since I caught Akane too, let's go home.

Hmm... It's true that Akane's is bigger, there's no doubt
about that.
Huh? But Hikaru is such a weakling.
Is there a reason why I must compete against a weakling?

Hehehe, I, the queen, Akane-sama, will specially play
against you.
Are you a kid or something!
I don't want to hear that from you!
Hehe, are you feeling like challenging the champ again?

The strong player and the weak player, it's
all determined by the will of the fish...
(I wonder who is the closest one?)
Ninnin. I have emerged victorious, I must say.
No way... for someone like me... to lose in the water...
It seems like your ninja training was lacking, ninnin.
Ugh... I don't even feel like retorting anymore.

Since I won, the winner shall exercise their rights as the
winner, I say.

The winner's rights? Is this the first time I'm hearing
about it!?
I did say it, in my heart.
What... you unexpectedly came up with a logical response.
Akane, you're smarter than I thought.

Are you trying to make me angry!?
I'm seriously getting angry, so...
Anyway, since I caught Akane too, let's go home.

Hmm... It's true that Akane's is bigger, there's no doubt
about that.
It seems that some pretty high-quality fish live here.
Ah, now that you mention it, I might have seen it.
I want to try eating it~ Can someone catch it for me?

Well, if you're talking about someone, it's only me and
Akane, right? The people who come fishing.
I want you to catch it.

If Hikaru, who defeated the champ, can catch it properly,
right?

But, you know, since I defeated the champ, wouldn't that
make me the champ?
Well, I don't really want to do that.
Well, I didn't say it out loud~

High-quality fish are really strong, huh~ Because they're high-
quality~
Ah, Hikaru, do you want to try again?
No, I want you to look at me too, not just the fish.
Good job! How do we eat it? Do we make it sashimi?
I can't do it at all!
Tsugumi-chan might be able to do it.

They seem like they can make something delicious, even if
it won't be sashimi.
Do you have the intention to make it yourself?
I can do retort food though!
Let's just leave it to the experts.

Later Tsugumi said, I've never cut fish like this before,
sounding unsure of herself, but...

The result wasn't bad, and since the ingredients were
good, the taste was also very wonderful.

It was the first time for everyone to eat live fish, and
it tasted so good that it was a pity there wasn't
any more...

I wonder if I can catch one more before going
home.
I want to eat it again.
Hikaru, hello~ I'm getting a tan today.
Hikaru, do you want to do it together?
Don't you want to? Too bad~
